## ✅ Lesson 8 — Request vs Response (Very Important Before API Automation)

Before writing API automation, you must clearly understand:

> What is Request
> What is Response
> What QA validates in each

In your **Philips HPM Support Tool**, every action is:

```
Request → API → Backend → Response
```

Without understanding this, API automation will be confusing.

---

## 🔹 1. What is Request

Request = What client sends to server

Client can be:

* WPF UI
* Support Tool
* Automation script
* Postman
* Playwright
* Python requests

Example:

```
POST /api/login
```

Request contains:

| Part    | Example             |
| ------- | ------------------- |
| URL     | /api/login          |
| Method  | POST                |
| Headers | token, content-type |
| Body    | username, password  |

Example request:

```http
POST /api/login
Content-Type: application/json
```

Body:

```json
{
  "username": "azeez",
  "password": "123"
}
```

This is request.

---

## 🔹 2. What is Response

Response = What server sends back

Response contains:

| Part        | Example      |
| ----------- | ------------ |
| Status code | 200          |
| Headers     | content-type |
| Body        | JSON         |

Example response:

```http
Status: 200
```

Body:

```json
{
  "token": "abc123",
  "role": "FSE"
}
```

This is response.

QA validates response.

---

## 🔹 3. Real Flow in HPM Support Tool

User clicks Login

```
UI → Request → API → Backend → DB → Response → UI
```

Example:

Request:

```
POST /login
```

Response:

```
token + role
```

Next request:

```
GET /features
```

Response:

```
features list
```

Next request:

```
GET /devices
```

Response:

```
device list
```

Everything works using request/response.

---

## 🔹 4. What QA checks in Request

QA checks:

✔ correct URL
✔ correct method
✔ correct headers
✔ correct body
✔ correct token
✔ correct role
✔ correct payload

Example bug:

Wrong request body

```
password missing
```

Expected:

```
400 error
```

QA must test this.

---

## 🔹 5. What QA checks in Response

QA checks:

✔ status code
✔ JSON structure
✔ data correct
✔ role correct
✔ permission correct
✔ DB match
✔ device match

Example:

```
GET /features
```

Response:

```json
{
  "role": "FSE",
  "features": ["enumerator"]
}
```

QA checks:

* role correct
* feature correct

---

## 🔹 6. Real Scenario — Role Based API

Request:

```
GET /features
Authorization: Bearer USER123
```

Response:

```json
{
  "features": ["dashboard"]
}
```

Request:

```
GET /features
Authorization: Bearer FSE123
```

Response:

```json
{
  "features": ["enumerator","connect","logs"]
}
```

Same request
Different response
Because header different.

Very common in your project.

---

## 🔹 7. Real Scenario — Device API

Request:

```
GET /devices
Authorization: Bearer FSE123
```

Response:

```json
[
  {"id":1,"status":"connected"}
]
```

QA checks:

* correct device
* correct status
* matches backend

Later we will validate with DB.

